Stephen Skory
May/June 2007
updated June 2008

This is a new implementation of hop for enzo datasets, to replace the old,
fragile 'enzohop.' This new enzohop uses plain HDF5 C++ calls
to extract the data, which is then fed into the hop mechanism. As far as I
know, this version is fine with 64 bit integers/floats, which enzohop isn't.

See http://mngrid.ucsd.edu/projects/enzo/wiki/enzohop for more information.